  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API + BackgroundService. Orchestrator is a scoped service (per request / per job).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Authorization happens at the endpoint layer (task 040) and job-handler layer (task 042). The orchestrator does NOT re-authorize — it assumes the caller is already authorized.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI registration via `AddActionEngineModule()` extension. Module total ≤15 non-framework registrations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Orchestrator type is internal to the Action Engine module. CRUD-side callers reach it via `IActionEngineFacade` (PublicContracts). G12 verified by grep audit.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tool dispatch audit emitted by `IToolHandlerRegistry` (task 026 — the choke point). Orchestrator emits per-Run audit on completion. Tier 2 hash + Tier 3 work history per dispatch; tenant scoping; GDPR erasure path. Task 043 extends middleware for Tool-dispatch enrichment.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-017">Run record status sequence `Queued → Running → Completed | Failed | Poisoned | Cancelled`. Orchestrator owns Running + terminal transitions. NO invented states.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Errors surfaced from the orchestrator as typed exceptions (e.g., `GateRejectedException`, `PhaseToolDeniedException` from task 025); endpoint layer translates to ProblemDetails.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">No new NuGet packages without budget verification. Reuse existing AI Search client + SK references.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist: placement = BFF, publish-size delta verified (module-level), no new CRUD→AI direct dependencies (facade enforces), no new HIGH-severity CVE.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">G12 facade integrity. No CRUD-side caller injects `IActionOrchestrationService` — verified by grep for the type outside `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/` (G12).</constraint>
  </constraints>

