  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, branch is `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes. Confirm tasks 026 (IToolHandlerRegistry), 030 (IGateResolver), 040 (ActionEndpoints) all show ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Load `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` and answer the pre-merge checklist in `notes/decisions/task-041-bff-extensions-checklist.md`. Cite placement = BFF (spec.md §6).</step>
    <step order="2">Read `AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs` to capture the structural shape. Read `IToolHandlerRegistry` (task 026 surface), `IGateResolver` (task 030 surface), `IAuditLogService` to understand the seams the orchestrator wires together.</step>
    <step order="3">Create `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/IActionOrchestrationService.cs`. Define `ExecuteActionAsync(ActionDefinition, IReadOnlyDictionary&lt;string, object&gt; parameters, ActionExecutionContext context, CancellationToken ct)`. The `ActionExecutionContext` carries `correlationId`, `tenantId`, `callerOid`, `phase` (default `execute`), `invocationSource` (Endpoint / ScheduledJob / MetaTool). Type is `internal` (or constrained to the Action Engine assembly).</step>
    <step order="4">Create `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ActionOrchestrationService.cs`. Constructor-inject: `IToolHandlerRegistry`, `IGateResolver`, `IAuditLogService`, `IActionRepository` (Dataverse read of Action Definition + Run write — typically the facade-internal repository from task 014/015), `ILogger&lt;ActionOrchestrationService&gt;`. Implement the 6-stage pipeline: load → validate-params → run-each-step (gate check → Tool dispatch → audit per ADR-015) → write Run terminal state.</step>
    <step order="5">Handle the canonical exceptions: `PhaseToolDeniedException` (from task 025) bubbles up with Run status `Failed`; `GateRejectedException` (from task 030) bubbles up with Run status `Failed` + reason; `OperationCanceledException` → Run status `Cancelled`. The endpoint layer (task 040) translates to ProblemDetails.</step>
    <step order="6">Run status transitions per ADR-017: caller sets `Queued`; orchestrator sets `Running` on entry; orchestrator sets terminal state (`Completed` / `Failed` / `Poisoned` / `Cancelled`) on exit. Use `IActionRunRepository.UpdateStatusAsync(runId, status, terminalDetails, ct)` for transitions.</step>
    <step order="7">Wire the `IActionEngineFacade` (task 015) implementation: `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/ActionEngineFacade.cs` (or wherever task 015 placed it) delegates `ExecuteActionAsync` to this orchestrator. The facade is the ONLY type outside `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/` allowed to reference `IActionOrchestrationService`. Document this boundary in a code comment AND in the file's top-of-file `&lt;remarks&gt;` XML doc.</step>
    <step order="8">DI registration: add `services.AddScoped&lt;IActionOrchestrationService, ActionOrchestrationService&gt;();` to `AddActionEngineModule()` (the extension created by task 014). Verify total non-framework registrations ≤15 per ADR-010.</step>
    <step order="9">Run the G12 grep audit: `grep -rn "IActionOrchestrationService" src/ --include="*.cs"` — expect references ONLY in `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/*.cs` and ONE reference in the facade implementation under `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/`. Record the verbatim grep output in `notes/spikes/g12-facade-integrity-grep.md`. If any reference is in `Services/Documents/`, `Api/` (other than tests), or elsewhere — that's a G12 violation, fix it before Step 9.5.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates per task-execute Step 9.5: `code-review` on the new service + interface + facade wiring; `adr-check` verifies ADR-010 (registration via module extension), ADR-013 (facade boundary preserved — G12), ADR-015 (audit emission at run-completion + delegation to IToolHandlerRegistry for per-dispatch audit), ADR-017 (status transitions canonical), ADR-029 (no new packages). Re-run `dotnet build` and unit-test scaffolding.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 041 ✅. Verify it unblocks tasks 042, 043, 052, 053, 054, 055, 060. Reset `current-task.md` for the next active task.</step>
    <step order="11">Document any deviations from this plan in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/task-041-handoff.md` and add a brief commit message recap.</step>
  </steps>

